name: Dynamic Power Management
author: Michaela Klauck <klauck@depend.uni-saarland.de>
description: A Modest MA model of a service provider that processes tasks of `N´ different types. Tasks to be processed are stored in one queue of maximum size `C´ for each task type. The service provider can be switched between three different power states (idle/busy, sleep and standby). The original model was translated from a MAPA file.

parameters.name: N
parameters.description: Number of different types of tasks

parameters.name: C
parameters.description: Maximum queue size for each task type

parameters.name: TIME_BOUND
parameters.description: The time bound for property PminQueuesFullBound

properties.name: PminQueuesFull
properties.description: The minimum probability for all queues to become full.

properties.name: PmaxQueuesFull
properties.description: The maximum probability for all queues to become full.

properties.name: PminQueue1Full
properties.description: The minimum probability for the queue of task type 1 to become full.

properties.name: PmaxQueue1Full
properties.description: The maximum probability for the queue of task type 1 to become full.

properties.name: TminQueuesFull
properties.description: The minimum expected time until all queues are full.

properties.name: PmaxQueuesFullBound
properties.description: The maximum probability for all queues to become full within the TIME-BOUND.

properties.name: SmaxQueuesFull
properties.description: Long-run probability that all queues are full.
